page.title: 20CREDITS
page.content: Ruislip is a prosperous area and the above pages reflect the relatively comfortable lifestyle.It hasn't always been so as a piece in the local paper called Wind of Change written by a resident showed.She has a great grand daughter at Whiteheath and we traced the family name of Lavender back to 1851.There is therefore continuity in an area of vast change in 50 years. {Editors (under 11 yrs)}K.Bower M.Fell P.Oxman B.Wales S.Taylor(+pages 17-20) {Writers (7-11yrs)}1 N.Modi,2 Bishop Ramsey(13 yrs) P.Budd 3 D.McNutt,4 E. Neep,5+6 G.Abel M.Smyth D.Cureton 7+8 Mrs Bunce's class 10 I.Braithwaite 11+12 S. Masters J.Bull A.Illingworth, 13+14 Bishop Ramsey,15 C.Taverner,16 S.Frame L.McCracken.{Primary Staff} A.
